This is probably old hat, but I have been unable to read all the posts since I reregistered.  I was thinking about either a new line of spells or replacing the Al'kabor line with a spell that you can cast on others (or hell self if you're crazy) that adds a proc.<br>
<br>
Start with Frost Spiral of Al'Kabor.  Retain damage, type (44 / cold) and the mana cost (100 mana) and make it a buff.  VI could then balance by adjusting the proc frequency.<br>
<br>
This would give us something that would make tanks love us, be useless for soloing, and would not be overpowering in the &quot;old&quot; world.  The procression of the Al'Kabor line means that we would have the ability to buff tanks with Magic, Cold, OR, Fire procs depending on situation.  <br>
<br>
Mildweasel<br>
53rd CT <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 1240<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/17/01 10:09 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What about a proccing effect we cast on Tanks?</span><hr size=1> I like the idea, but again that's enchanter land.  Like the silence spell and the suppress casting, that's enchantments.  Wizards aren't real subtle. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwraithwavefeaamael.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wraithwave FeaAmael</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 431<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/17/01 3:11 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What about a proccing effect we cast on Tanks?</span><hr size=1> I actually believe it depends on the nature of the proc.  Damage shields are all over the place.  But for druids its based on...  A SHRUBBERY!!!!!   psyche wait...   Druids its based on thorns, etc...  but for casters its based on fire.  Bards actually have a couple different varieties.<br>
<br>
Perhaps we can imbue other classes weapons with maybe True North or Eye of Zomm.  What do you think?<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Very sorry, I am just about to leave work for the day and I am VERY PUNCHY right now.<br>
<br>
I think with a certain amount of concentrated effort, VI could come up with one single Imbuing spell where we create some kind of proccing effect on others.  The problem is, it would have to be SO POWERFUL to get other classes to even LOOK at us.  And then, it would be a balancing issue of course.<br>
<br>
W.F. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=mildweasel>Mildweasel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/18/01 5:52 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What about a proccing effect we cast on Tanks?</span><hr size=1> <br>
Hate to disagree Grim, but I don't think castable procs belongs to any class.  Rogues do it with poison, Rangers have call of Sky, Necros and SKs have a couple of spells that do this, but it isnt a major part of any classes repetoire that I know of.<br>
<br>
To Wraith's point:  Yes damage would have to be significant at high levels and it would require some tuning I am sure.  What I am looking for is some way to boost our damage output without making us even more leathal as solo artists.  Something that would make Tanks WANT to group with a wizard.<br>
<br>
Mildweasel <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=mookus>Mookus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 100<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/18/01 7:03 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ..</span><hr size=1> I think speculating as to what this non damage related wizard grouping ability can only lead to dissappointment, but adding a callofearth type buff to the wizard would be an even bigger letdown than what i could imagine.<br>
<br>
How about if wizards could tp a mob back to it's spawn point with a memblur.... that would be nice. Or a group harvest that gives all members some mana. Or indoor harmony. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 1259<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/18/01 8:29 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ..</span><hr size=1> Here's the problem Mildweasel: Several classes now have this, Verant added it to all the Hybrids very recently.  But when you read the description of the Enchanter class it says &quot;ABLE TO ENCHANT WEAPONS AND ARMOR&quot; neither of which the Enchanter can do.<br>
<br>
See, its not so much nobody better ever have this ability... it's that Enchanters DON'T have this ability and of all the possible things they should have, out of the bizarre hundreds of abilities they got thrown together, ENCHANTERS CAN'T ENCHANT.  So before we or any other class gets this, Enchanters should get it first, best, and most. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=mildweasel>Mildweasel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/18/01 10:04 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Again I must disagree</span><hr size=1> <br>
Sorry Grimstaff I think you are barking up the wrong tree with the enchant.  From everything I understand the &quot;Enchant Weapons and Armour&quot; pertains to _craft_ skills.  ie the various enchant metal spells and now the tailoring that requires the mana vials.  As a grandmaster smith and master tailor I tend to keep track of what those extortionist in robes...I mean enchanters can and cant do craft wise<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Couple years ago the Wu Gloves recipe was put in specifically to address the lack of anything that Enchanters could enchant.  The promise was never that they could enchant weapons and such IN COMBAT, but rather that they would have a role in smithing and tailoring magic items (actually VI said that you NEEDED Enchanters to make magic smithed and tailored items).<br>
<br>
Mildweasel<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uakkronn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Akkronn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/18/01 11:06 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Again I must disagree</span><hr size=1> MOOKUS<br>
/*************************************************<br>
How about if wizards could tp a mob back to it's spawn point with a memblur.... that would be nice. Or a group harvest that gives all members some mana. Or indoor harmony. <br>
*************************************************/<br>
<br>
    I like this idea alot, Transloc mob to is spawn whit memblur efect is a creative idea and fit whit the master of teleportation Verant like to put in wizard head.<br>
<br>
  For mana regen, why dont give wizard a special ability, something like LoH but for mana. One per day being able to addd lot of mana on a target or on the caster.<br>
<br>
 <p>Akkronn Highcaster
Gnome wizard
Karana server</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 1261<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/18/01 11:06 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Again I must disagree</span><hr size=1> You may understand that but Enchanters don't.  And really, without wanting this for Wizards yourself, can you seriously look an Enchanter in the eye and say with a straight face &quot;You shouldn't have this spell first, it doesn't enchant the weapons of the person buffed.&quot;<br>
<br>
Seriously now, it is enchanter territory, you are giving the person an ENCHANTMENT that makes their weapons do something they didn't before.  That's EXACTLY the concept that everyone (but Verant apparently) has for the class and what they think of when they see the description. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uflintnilf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Flintnilf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/18/01 1:58 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Again I must disagree</span><hr size=1> You are Imbueing magic/fire/cold (depending on level) into the weapon.  Forget about Imbue Fire Opal?<br>
<br>
What about all the Imbues that belong to all the other non-chanter classes?<br>
<br>
And it's NOT a damage shield, so don't confuse it with one.  This damage/proc occurs when the tank hits the mob, not when the mob hits the tank. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 1270<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/18/01 2:17 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Again I must disagree</span><hr size=1> Enchanters have MANY imbue spells, they have the most of any class.  This would be something they do NOT have. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=mildweasel>Mildweasel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/18/01 9:37 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Again I must disagree</span><hr size=1> <br>
True Grim, but they don't have very good offensive damage dealers and this could legitimatly be an exception.  Just as Druids get ports at least as good as ours, but have NO planes ports.  <br>
<br>
Or a better example would be call of the hero.  A transport spell, yet because of its nature deemed to be under the Mages aegis<br>
<br>
Mildweasel (also a slightly tipsy weasel at moment) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwraithwavefeaamael.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wraithwave FeaAmael</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 451<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/18/01 10:14 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Again I must disagree</span><hr size=1> There is pleanty of class crossing that goes on already.  Whether it is ports, Imbuing, damage shields, buffs, heals, whatever.  As far as i am concerned, there is nothing inappropraite about adding one more.  The problem is always the same however...   the aftereffect of other class complaints about whatever the change is.<br>
<br>
How many remember how much the IVU classes were enraged when we received a self invis vs undead spell?<br>
<br>
